      "text": "# Dominion Energy details its $65B, five-year spending plan | Utility Dive\n\nPublished: 2026-02-24T17:27:36+00:00\nAuthor: Brian Martucci\n\n## Summary\n\nDominion Energy's utility business saw strong growth in electricity demand last year, with the larger of its two regulated utilities, Dominion Energy Virginia, leading with 5.4% weather-normalized sales growth. The company expects further growth in its territory, with a 4.9% increase over the next 15 years. To meet new data center demand, Dominion plans to spend roughly $65 billion through 2030 on a combined rate base projected to grow 10.2% annually. Approximately 75% of this spending will involve transmission and distribution infrastructure, with an additional 18% for new gas generation. The firm also plans to invest in solar and energy storage spending, supported by Virginia’s clean energy framework, and may expand its ambitious spending plans after 2030.\n\n## Story\n\nDominion Energy details its $65B, five-year spending plan | Utility Div",
